From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v31 - remove bridge_disable to keep HDMI signal

After v28's adjusted_clock fallback let CRTC mode_set succeed, the
display went DARK (backlight off).  In v26 with mode_set failing,
backlight was on (because bridge was running but CRTC didn't program
GPU TX).  Diagnosis: when mode_set succeeds, drm_crtc_helper_set_mode
calls bridge_disable BEFORE the GPU reprograms DP TX, then
bridge_enable after.  The disable mutes the bridge (VMUTECNT
sequence in ps4_bridge_disable), then GPU TX changes its output,
then bridge_enable tries to re-lock to the new signal.  Empirically
the bridge fails to re-lock -> no HDMI output.

Workaround: remove .disable and .post_disable from ps4_bridge_funcs
so the bridge stays running with its last good config through the
GPU reprogramming.  The post-GPU bridge_enable then layers on top
of an already-active bridge.

If v31 works:
- backlight stays on across DRM modeset cycles
- bridge_enable runs without preceding disable
- HDMI shows actual content (lightdm / TTY)

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
@@ -805,8 +805,13 @@
 static struct drm_bridge_funcs ps4_bridge_funcs = {
 	.pre_enable = ps4_bridge_pre_enable,
 	.enable = ps4_bridge_enable,
-	.disable = ps4_bridge_disable,
-	.post_disable = ps4_bridge_post_disable,
+	/* v31: bridge_disable + post_disable removed.  When CRTC mode_set
+	 * runs (v28 fallback makes it succeed), DRM modeset chain calls
+	 * bridge_disable -> mutes the bridge (VMUTECNT), then GPU
+	 * reprograms DP TX, then bridge_enable runs.  Empirically the
+	 * post-GPU enable doesn't restore HDMI signal -> backlight goes
+	 * off.  Removing the disable callback keeps the bridge running
+	 * (last good config) through the GPU reprogramming. */
 	.attach = ps4_bridge_attach,
 	.mode_fixup = ps4_bridge_mode_fixup,
 	.mode_set = ps4_bridge_mode_set,
